added.title: The Slip
added.description: Richard doesn't answer the door in time and the jobsworth delivery guy will not let him have his package. His options are to pick his package up at the depot or pay for a redelivery. Richard doesn't like the sound of either option, so a battle of wills begins that can only end in the destruction of one or both of them.

added.title: The Grades
added.description: Miss Simian discovers a failed test from Gumball's past that brings down his grade point average. This means he has to retake kindergarten all over again, much to her delight. But by demoting him Miss Simian has inadvertently brought herself down, and they're left with no choice but to team up if they want things back to normal.

added.title: The Ex
added.description: Gumball discovers that Rob, his old nemesis, is "neme-seeing" someone else now. Devastated that Rob has fallen out of hate with him, Gumball refuses to accept that his ex-nemesis has moved on and does his best to sabotage Rob's blossoming relationship with his new foe, Banana Joe.

added.title: The Blame
added.description: Gumball gives Billy his first taste of videogames but the sheer excitement causes him to pass out. His mother Felicity summons the PTA and threatens to ban video games all across Elmore. Gumball and Darwin are given three chances to prove that videogames can be a force for good. But when they fail, they decide to prove books can be just as dangerous.

added.title: The Detective
added.description: Anais arrives in the bedroom to find a messy crime-scene and her Daisy doll missing. She realizes Gumball and Darwin are the chief suspects. Following a series of clues is her only chance to track them down and her only hope of learning what happened to Daisy. But as the mystery unravels, it seems the culprits may have turned on each other.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Too Short to Ride
added.description: Steven and Amethyst take a trip to Funland but run into trouble when their friend is too short to ride the rollercoasters.

added.title: Beach City Drift
added.description: Steven and Connie get into a high-speed car race with their biggest foe.

added.title: Kiki's Pizza Delivery Service
added.description: Steven saves Kiki from some delicious nightmares.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Normal Man
added.description: Stripped of his magic powers, Normal Man enlists Finn and Jake's help to rescue his brother Glob.

added.title: A King's Ransom
added.description: Ice King suffers a heartbreaking loss and it's up to Finn and Jake to find the culprit.

added.title: Date with Gus
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve accidentally ruin Mr. Gus' night, the two of them go undercover as Mr. Gus's date.

added.title: Gone to His Head
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's new found confidence makes his head big.

added.title: Lame Station
added.description: Pizza Steve tries desperately to make the others in the RV interested in his new game console.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Clarence for President
added.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

added.title: Butt Dial
added.description: Mordecai pocket dials an embarrassing message on Margaret's phone.

added.title: Gut Model
added.description: Muscle Man becomes a model.

added.title: Big Winner
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby give Muscle Man a lottery ticket for his birthday.

added.title: Replaced
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that Benson is going to replace them and have to figure out a way to stop it.

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Fists of Justice
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to do all of Skips' duties for the day.

added.title: Loyalty to the King
added.description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's number one fan gets more than he bargained for when Uncle Grandpa overstays his welcome.

added.title: The Chamber of Frozen Blades
added.description: In Ninja-mode, Finn and Jake break into Ice King's palace to catch him red-handed.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Enchiridion
added.description: Finn quests for a book that will make him a better hero.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
added.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

added.title: Bad Heir Day
added.description: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.

removed.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
removed.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

removed.title: While You Were Away
removed.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

removed.title: Vilgax Must Croak
removed.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

removed.description: A compilation of some of the funniest, most bizarre clips uploaded onto the internet by the people of Elmore. Clips include Banana Joe's self-choreographed acrobatics, Richard's latest culinary invention and Gumball and Darwin's contest for who can pull the weirdest face.

removed.title: Cloris
removed.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

removed.title: Back to the Library

removed.title: Same Old World
removed.description: Steven flies around the world.

removed.title: Message Received
removed.description: Steven has doubts about believing in everyone.

removed.title: Mordecai and Rigby Down Under
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to catch a flight to the USA.

removed.title: The Menu
removed.description: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell them what it's called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

removed.title: Ugly Moons
removed.description: Muscle Man vows to prank someone.

removed.title: Tummy Trouble
removed.description: When the Incursean armada kidnaps the Gourmand Queen, Ben and Rook must get the warring Gormand factions to work together to save her and stop the Incursean invasion.

removed.title: Belly Bros
removed.description: When a kid is bummed that his favorite shirt won't fit over his big belly, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to show him that t-shirts come and go, but having a big belly is always cool.

removed.title: Chimney
removed.description: While playing in the woods the boys befriend a wild dog, bring it home and name it Chimney. When the boys find themselves trapped in a well, the new pup is their only hope for escape.

removed.title: James
removed.description: Finn & Jake are excited when Princess Bubblegum invites them to help her collect samples in the Desert of Wonders. But when their vessel is attacked by nasty goo monsters, Finn & Jake start to think the mission has been sabotaged by PB's robot helper James.

removed.title: Beyond This Earthly Realm
removed.description: When Finn finds a porcelain lamb, it transports him into the spirit world - and only the Ice King can help get him out!

removed.title: Get That BORFL!
removed.description: A restful chill day for the Warriors and Princess Zange in the Royal Spa gets upended when a cute little Borfl runs amok throughout Castle Rhyboflaven, with the Warriors resorting to Magiswords to thwart the critter.

removed.title: The Interrogation
removed.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

removed.title: Birthday Gift
removed.description: Rigby always gives Mordecai the worst birthday gifts, but this year it's going to be different.

removed.title: The Weirdo
removed.description: When they see the school bullies making fun of Sussie, Gumball and Darwin decide to try and help her act less weird. They carefully observe her behavior and decide that the only thing they have to change is absolutely everything.

removed.title: Shower Party
removed.description: Things get out of hand when Andrew W. K. helps Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus throw a party while Uncle Grandpa is in the shower.

removed.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
removed.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

removed.title: Donny
removed.description: In an attempt to save a village, Finn and Jake rehabilitate Donny the Ogre, who's a real jerk.

removed.title: Super Watermelon Island
removed.description: Steven finds out what happened to all those sentient watermelons he created.

removed.title: Hit the Diamond
removed.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

removed.title: Puddle Eyes
removed.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

removed.title: You Can't Handle the Tooth
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus must rescue Pizza Steve from the Tooth Fairy.

removed.title: Special Delivery
removed.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

removed.title: What's the Big Idea?
removed.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

removed.title: Lost Playground
removed.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

removed.title: Heat Signature
removed.description: Marceline messes with Finn & Jake and tells them they're vampires, but maybe this joke has gone too far.

removed.title: Dumptown USA
removed.description: Benson is going to fire Mordecai if Rigby can't bring him back from a bizarre land of dudes also known as Dumptown USA.

removed.title: Thank You
removed.description: The Snow Golem and his beseeching pup pay a visit to the Fire Kingdom.
